  2. Oxford 15

Words 1401-1500

  1. invent
    Thomas Edison helped invent the electric light bulb.

  2. invention
    The telephone was a great invention of its time.

  3. invest
    She decided to invest her money in a new business.

  4. investigate
    The police will investigate the cause of the fire.

  5. investigation
    The investigation revealed important details about the case.

  6. investment
    Buying a house is a big investment for most people.

  7. invitation
    I received an invitation to her birthday party.

  8. invite
    They will invite all their friends to the wedding.

  9. involve
    The project will involve many hours of hard work.

  10. involved
    He was deeply involved in the community project.

  11. iron
    She used an iron to press her clothes.

  12. island
    They spent their vacation on a beautiful island.

  13. issue
    The magazine covers a wide range of social issues.

  14. IT
    He works in the IT department of a large company.

  15. it
    It is raining outside, so take an umbrella.

  16. item
    This item is on sale for half price today.

  17. its
    The dog wagged its tail happily.

  18. itself
    The cat cleaned itself after eating.

  19. jacket
    He wore a warm jacket because it was cold.

  20. jam
    She spread strawberry jam on her toast.

  21. January
    The new year begins in January.

  22. jazz
    They enjoy listening to jazz music in the evenings.

  23. jeans
    She bought a new pair of blue jeans.

  24. jewellery
    The shop sells beautiful gold and silver jewellery.

  25. job
    He found a new job at a local company.

  26. join
    Would you like to join us for dinner tonight?

  27. joke
    He told a funny joke that made everyone laugh.

  28. journal
    She writes in her journal every night before bed.

  29. journalist
    The journalist interviewed the mayor for the article.

  30. journey
    Their journey to the mountains took several hours.

  31. joy
    The children’s laughter brought joy to the room.

  32. judge
    The judge listened carefully to both sides of the argument.

  33. judgement
    Her judgement was fair and thoughtful.

  34. juice
    He drank a glass of orange juice with breakfast.

  35. July
    They plan to visit the beach in July.

  36. jump
    The cat can jump very high to catch the ball.

  37. June
    The school year ends in June.

  38. junior
    She is a junior member of the team.

  39. just
    I just finished reading the book you gave me.

  40. justice
    The lawyer fought for justice in the courtroom.

  41. justify
    He tried to justify his actions to his friends.

  42. keen
    She is very keen to learn new skills.

  43. keep
    Please keep this book safe for me.

  44. key
    He lost the key to his car.

  45. keyboard
    She typed the letter on her computer keyboard.

  46. kick
    He gave the ball a strong kick during the game.

  47. kid
    The kid was excited to see the animals at the zoo.

  48. kill
    The pesticide is used to kill harmful insects.

  49. killing
    The killing of innocent animals is a serious issue.

  50. kilometre
    The town is located about 10 kilometres from here.

  51. kind
    She is always kind to everyone she meets.

  52. king
    The king ruled the country for many years.

  53. kiss
    She gave her mother a kiss before leaving.

  54. kitchen
    The kitchen was filled with the smell of fresh bread.

  55. knee
    He hurt his knee while playing football.

  56. knife
    She used a sharp knife to cut the vegetables.

  57. knock
    There was a loud knock at the door.

  58. know
    I know the answer to that question.

  59. knowledge
    Reading books can increase your knowledge.

  60. lab
    The students conducted experiments in the science lab.

  61. label
    The label on the bottle shows the ingredients.

  62. laboratory
    The laboratory is equipped with modern tools for research.

  63. labour
    The workers were rewarded for their hard labour.

  64. lack
    The project failed due to a lack of resources.

  65. lady
    The lady at the counter was very helpful.

  66. lake
    They went fishing at the lake last weekend.

  67. lamp
    She turned on the lamp to read her book.

  68. land
    The plane will land at the airport in an hour.

  69. landscape
    The artist painted a beautiful landscape of the mountains.

  70. language
    English is a widely spoken language around the world.

  71. laptop
    He uses his laptop to complete his work.

  72. large
    They live in a large house near the park.

  73. largely
    The success of the event was largely due to her efforts.

  74. last1
    This is the last chance to buy tickets for the show.

  75. late
    She arrived late to the meeting because of traffic.

  76. later
    We can discuss this matter later in the day.

  77. latest
    Have you seen the latest movie in the series?

  78. laugh
    The joke made everyone laugh out loud.

  79. laughter
    The room was filled with the sound of laughter.

  80. launch
    The company will launch its new product next month.

  81. law
    Everyone must follow the law to maintain order.

  82. lawyer
    The lawyer prepared the case for the trial.

  83. lay
    She lay the book on the table and left the room.

  84. layer
    The cake has a thick layer of chocolate on top.

  85. lazy
    He felt lazy and decided to stay in bed all day.

  86. lead1
    She will lead the team in the upcoming project.

  87. leader
    The leader of the group gave a motivating speech.

  88. leadership
    Good leadership is essential for the success of any team.

  89. leading
    She is a leading expert in her field of study.

  90. leaf
    The tree lost its last leaf in the autumn wind.

  91. league
    Their team won the football league this year.

  92. lean
    He had to lean on the wall to keep his balance.

  93. learn
    She wants to learn how to play the guitar.

  94. learning
    Learning a new language can be challenging but rewarding.

  95. least
    This is the least expensive option available.

  96. leather
    He bought a leather jacket from the store.

  97. leave
    They will leave for the airport early in the morning.

  98. lecture
    The professor gave an interesting lecture on history.

  99. left
    She turned left at the corner to reach the park.

  100. leg
    He broke his leg while skiing last winter.
